    "summary": "On 13-January-2021 at approximately 2315 hrs, a gas release from failed packing on recycle valve FCV-1053B caused a facility muster and emergency shutdown on MC 809 A-Ursa. Gas detectors functioned properly and triggered alarms. The ESD system operated as designed. No equipment damage or injuries occurred. The failed packing was replaced and the valve was successfully tested.",
